<TEXT>
a bus driver yelled i have no brakes 
moments before a city bus slid off a winding stretch of road and 
plunged down a 60foot cliff killing 19 people and injuring 22 
authorities said 
the accident monday occurred about four miles from downtown on a 
curved steep portion of road on the outskirts of this baja 
california resort fire department officials said 
of the 22 injured treated at local hospitals several were said 
to be in critical condition said miroslava cuellar a spokeswoman 
for the city of ensenada 
the bus operated by the rojo y blanco line had not had a 
mechanical inspection in five years and had no insurance as required 
by state law cuellar said 
it is wellknown that there is corruption between the transport 
companies and state transit officials she said considering 
that these vehicles are allowed to operate without inspections and 
without insurance and that drivers are paid not a salary but by the 
number of passengers they can cram into their buses it is clear 
there is corruption 
the bus driver and 13 passengers died in the accident five more 
passengers died at hospitals on monday and tuesday chavez said 
a spokesman for the fire department jose luis chavez said bus 
driver enrique hernandez de jesus apparently lost control of the 
vehicle while trying to negotiate the curve 
one surviving passenger reportedly told investigators that the 
bus driver said hang on tight i have no brakes moments before 
the bus slid over the cliff 
chavez said he hoped the tragedy would bring an investigation of 
bus transit practices in ensenada he said some of the buses were so 
unworthy that they were no better than coffins on wheels 
a woman who lives about 200 yards from the accident scene said 
she ran to see what happened after hearing a tremendous crash 
it was a horror scene said leticia perez de la rosa 
people were screaming begging for help and i started to cry 
a mass funeral service is planned wednesday for the dead said 
ramon moreno owner of a funeral home that is handling the 
arrangements 
