<TEXT>
jury deliberations began tuesday in the murder 
trial of billy glaze who was depicted by the prosecution as a 
pathological killer still savoring the ghoulish murders of three 
american indian women 
he hated women and he particularly hated indian women 
prosecutor pete connors told the jury of eight women and four men in 
his closing argument he had a fury in his gut he wanted to hurt 
them and hurt them badly and he wanted to kill them and to have them 
die in anguish 
mr glaze had hellish fantasies that he couldnt keep to 
himself and he acted on them connors said 
defense attorney michael colich decried the lack of physical 
evidence in the case and attacked the credibility of prosecution 
witnesses the witnesses placed glaze at the scenes of two slayings 
and in the presence of the three victims before their deaths 
the jury which got the case tuesday afternoon after 11 days of 
testimony retired for the night and was to resume deliberations 
wednesday 
glaze 45 a drifter who pretended he was an american indian 
went on trial jan 23 on six counts of firstdegree murder in the 
sexual mutilation and slayings of kathleen bullman 19 angeline 
whitebirdsweet 27 and angela green 26 in 1986 and 1987 in 
minneapolis 
colich who called only four witnesses compared with 70 brought 
by the prosecution characterized glaze as a nonviolent drifter who 
called attention to himself by saying despicable things about women 
he said police were not thorough in their investigation of other 
suspects because of public pressure to solve the serial killings 
not one piece of evidence points to billy glaze but because he 
has a bad mouth and because he left town they think he did it 
colich said they police and prosecutors are going to get that 
man if its the last thing they do 
connors told the jury that glaze killed the three women in 
similar fashion leaving their nude bodies in places where they 
could easily be found the identical way in which the bodies were 
sexually mutilated proved that a pathological killer was responsible 
for the deaths connors said 
he killed these women in an unbelievably ghoulish fashion and 
hes sitting in jail enjoying it connors said 
the prosecutor reminded the jury of testimony from former prison 
acquaintances of glaze who said he admitted to the killings he also 
displayed a note written by glaze that said i killed them i was 
mad at them 
