says trees talk in signals that he calls wwaves 
explaining the phenomenon wagner pointed to a blip on a chart 
recording a tree being chopped it put out a tremendous cry of 
alarm he said the adjacent trees put out smaller ones 
an abstract of his research was published last fall in northwest 
science magazine 
wagner 58 holds a doctorate in physics from the university of 
