<TEXT>
ron field a tony and emmy award winning director 
and choreographer who developed routines for dancers ranging from 
fred astaire to michael jackson has died at age 55 
field died monday at st vincents hospital of neurological 
impairment due to brain lesions he had lived in manhattan 
fields career began in 1942 when as an 8yearold he appeared 
with gertrude lawrence on broadway in lady in the dark he also 
danced in numerous broadway shows early in his career including 
gentlemen prefer blondes and kismet 
besides jackson and astaire field choreographed gene kelly ray 
bolger ben vereen mikhail baryshnikov cyd charisse debbie allen 
carol lawrence chita rivera sandy duncan marge champion shirley 
maclaine debbie reynolds raquel welch annmargret liza minnelli 
bernadette peters tommy tune and others 
he won tony awards for his work as director and choreographer of 
the broadway musical applause starring lauren bacall 
fields choreography for zorba and most recently rags 
resulted in additional tony nominations 
fields other broadway credits as director and choreographer 
include king of hearts and the revivals of on the town and 
peter pan 
he won emmys for choreographing such shows as ben vereen 
his roots america salutes richard rodgers and baryshnikov 
on broadway which won a record nine emmys 
he also directed carol burnett in once upon a mattress danny 
kaye and ms duncan in pinocchio and dean jones and teri garr 
in the brothers grimm 
field also was responsible for the dances and musical staging of 
five years of the academy awards presentations three years of the 
tony awards and three years of the emmy awards 
besides his work in theater and television field has produced 
and staged productions for venues ranging from the casino de paris 
to the casino du liban in beirut to the 1984 worlds fair in new 
orleans 
field made his choreographic opera debut with the new york city 
opera premier of ashmedai and worked with director martin 
scorcese on the robert de niroms minnelli movie new york new 
york 
in 1984 choreographed the spectacular show at the los angeles 
olympics that included 3300 dancers singers and musicians at the 
opening ceremonies 
at his death field was working on a new production a musical 
entitled sound stage 10 
fields choreography can be seen in the current national tour of 
cabaret starring joel grey 
he is survived by his mother meta adorf of chula vista calif 
and his father harry field 
funeral arrangements were not completed but attorney michael 
miller said a memorial will be staged within six weeks at a broadway 
theater 
