largest daily asked tuesday the detainees protest should cause 
all south africans to think anew about the deprivation of basic 
human rights which continues on so gross a scale 
the prison service confirmed the hunger strike but the law and 
order ministry declined to comment 
in johannesburg cape town and durban meanwhile white women 
held news conferences to demand that white men be given the choice 
to perform community service rather than military duty 
white men must serve two years of initial training then can be 
called up for up to three months a year in recent years some 
conscripts have been sent to quell unrest in black townships 
township duty is not defending my country from some foreign 
force complained scotty morton of cape town who said her son was 
hospitalized for depression during his military service 
our sons are being used against my fellow countrymen who 
are angrily protesting against unjust and discriminatory laws she 
said 
judy bester whose son is serving a sixyear prison term for 
refusing to serve noted in johannesburg that president pw botha 
never served in the military botha was single and in his early 20s 
during world war ii when thousands of south africans fought for the 
allies 
military service by nonwhites is voluntary 
also students at a soweto high school said at least 12 pupils 
were injured monday when police using whips and batons broke up a 
