south and north korea bitter rivals 
since the division of the peninsula 44 years ago open political 
talks wednesday to prepare for the first meeting of their prime 
ministers 
if they take place the prime ministerial talks will be the 
highest level held between the two koreas they are aimed at easing 
tensions by resolving political and military disputes 
fivemember delegations each headed by a vice minister are to 
meet at the truce village of panmunjom to negotiate terms for the 
talks 
two days later lawmakers of the two sides are to meet for an 
eighth round of talks on a nonaggression pact 
preparations also are under way to open another channel of 
dialogue in march this time for sports officials who want to form a 
single korean team for the 1990 asian games in beijing china 
the flurry of talks comes at a time when relations between the 
countries are undergoing changes after many years of bitter 
competition 
we are getting mixed signals from north korea said kim 
namsik a south korean who specializes in north koean affairs 
although they seem flexible on some issues their basic positions 
are still very strong and show no sign of change he said 
professor lee hojae of seouls korea university said north 
korea appears to be changing but the change is very slow and would 
not bring a rapid improvement of relations with south korea 
last week the communist government signed an unprecedented 
agreement with a south korean industrialist to undertake several 
joint ventures including a major tourist complex but it was 
unclear whether the business agreement indicated a policy change 
toward seoul 
any such changes will be tested when north koreas military and 
political officials sit down with their south korean partners 
wednesday to discuss highly sensitive issues such as the us 
military presence in the south 
north korea has indicated repeatedly it will call off scheduled 
meetings unless joint ussouth korea military exercises are 
halted the exercises normally start in february and last about two 
months 
pyongyang suspended all dialogue with seoul in 1986 to protest 
the maneuvers an annual event since 1976 
the us command in seoul last week refused to confirm or deny 
whether maneuvers have begun but said officials of the two 
countries began planning on the training many months ago and 
that planning continues 
in the past the maneuvers were announced well in advance but 
this year a formal announcement is being delayed at seouls request 
south korean defense minister lee sanghoon said last week the 
scale and format of the exercises could be reduced if north korea 
shows a concrete change of attitude 
military officials of the united states and south korea say the 
exercises are needed to deter a possible invasion by north korea 
pyongyangs forces ivnaded south korea in 1950 starting a 
threeyear war 
the highlevel talks first were proposed by north korea on nov 
16 
north korea said the main agenda should include the withdrawal by 
1991 of the 42000 us troops stationed in south korea and a 
reduction of the two koreas armed forces to 100000 each by the 
same year 
south korea has an estimated 650000 men under arms and north 
korea about 850000 
