congress voted overwhelmingly tuesday to turn 
down its 51 percent pay raise and rushed the legislation to 
president bush who signed it hours before a midnight deadline 
lawmakers were anxious to end the public outcry against the 
45500 increase which left them feeling in the words of one 
representative like cannon fodder for trash television and talk 
