members to set aside partisan differences and work with dispatch to 
report a bill to the full senate 
this problem is serious enough that we dont have time to be 
partisan about it garn said i hope we can get together in the 
next few months to pass legislation 
volcker said the problem was of such a serious nature that if 
necessary congress should consider exempting the necessary 
government spending from the overall deficit limits established by 
the grammrudman balancedbudget law 
he said this could be justified because sale of the government 
bonds being used to finance the bailout effort was different from 
