<TEXT>
polaroid corp on tuesday posted a 75 
million loss in the fourth quarter of 1988 it attributed to the 
costs of a corporate restructuring earlier in the year 
polaroid which has been battling to fend off a hostile takeover 
bid by shamrock holdings inc said sales for the period totaled 
533 million up 47 percent from 509 million in the corresponding 
1987 quarter 
the loss included a 549 million charge to cover remaining costs 
the restructuring which included elimination of 1300 workers under 
a voluntary severance plan planned global distribution of 35mm film 
and a 300 million employee stock ownership plan 
the loss compared to earnings of 423 million in the same 
quarter the previous year 
for the full year polaroid said it lost 226 million on sales 
of 186 billion compared with earnings of 125 million or 202 
cents a share on revenue of 176 billion in 1987 
the full year figures include a 152 million charge for the 
restructuring which was announced in july and other expenses to 
fend off disney familyowned shamrock the instant camera company 
said 
</TEXT>
