<TEXT>
gte corp on tuesday said fourthquarter 
earnings for 1988 were down 2 percent from the same period the 
previous year when the telecommunications company benefited from a 
property sale that boosted net income for the quarter by 26 million 
the company reported fourthquarter net income of 326 million 
or 96 cents a share on consolidated revenues and sales of 43 
billion compared to net income of 334 million or 99 cents a 
share on consolidated revenues of 41 billion for the same period 
a year ago 
excluding nonoperating items quarterly profits would have risen 
6 percent gte said 
for the full year net income rose 9 percent to a recordhigh 
12 billion compared to 11 billion earned in 1987 earnings per 
share totaled 358 also up 9 percent over the 329 reported a 
year ago consolidated 1988 revenues and sales were 165 billion 7 
percent more than the 154 billion reported for 1987 
james l johnson gte chairman and chief executive noted that 
the price of gte stock rose by 26 percent in 1988 and said the 
company has taken several steps to enhance future earnings growth 
these included reducing our holdings in us sprint and in our 
networkswitching business divesting certain other businesses not 
earning an adequate return as wellin a prepared statement 
</TEXT>
