<TEXT>
plessey co plc on tuesday rejected as 
outrageous a revised proposal by britains general electric co 
plc and west germanys siemens ag aimed at obtaining british 
government approval for a joint bid for plessey 
this is absolutely no way to decide on the future of key 
sectors of the british and european electronics industry stephen 
walls plesseys managing director said in a statement 
gec and siemens announced new proposals monday for dividing up 
various plessey businesses should their takeover bid for the 
electronics and defense contractor succeed 
the revised plan submitted to the monopolies and mergers 
commission which is investigating the bid was an attempt to calm 
british government concerns about maintaining competition in the 
electronics industry 
walls called the new restructuring proposals a good 
oldfashioned carveup of an aggressive competitor by two tired 
european monolithic enterprises 
the plessey official also complained about the timing of the 
move which provided only the minimum amount of time for proper 
discussion and review 
the 296 billion bid for plessey was referred to the monopolies 
commission nearly a month ago the commission was given three months 
to conclude its investigation and decide whether the bid should be 
allowed to procede 
</TEXT>
