<TEXT>
former secretary of state george shultz and the 
president of california institute of technology were elected to 
general motors corps board of directors tuesday 
shultz and thomas everhart were elected during a gm board meeting 
in new york the company said in a news release issued here 
shultz 68 first was elected to the gm board in 1981 when he was 
president of the bechtel group inc an engineering construction 
and management services company he resigned from the gm board a 
year later to become secretary of state 
everhart 56 has been president of cal tech since 1987 before 
that he held several positions in engineering instruction and 
college administration 
</TEXT>
